title: Facebook prepares legal action against Thai government's request to block group
text: Facebook said it is planning legal action against Thailand's demand that forced the company to block a group deemed critical of the country's monarchy.

title: Facebook France to pay over £95 million in back taxes
text: Facebook Inc. (NASDAQ: FB) said on Monday that its French subsidiary will pay over £95 million in back taxes.

title: RBC's Mark Mahaney on TikTok's advantage compared to other social media companies
text: TikTok is suing the U.S. government, challenging the Trump administration's efforts to ban the company's American operations.

title: Mark Zuckerberg told US government TikTok is a threat to American business: Report
text: Yahoo Finance's Aikiko Fujita breaks down the report that Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg told President Trump and other lawmakers that TikTok is a threat to the United States.

title: Facebook to pay $125 million in back taxes in France, report says
text: Facebook France is going to pay $125 million (€106 million) in back taxes according to business magazine Capital — Facebook confirmed the agreement to both Capital and Reuters. French tax authorities raided Facebook’s offices in Paris in 2012 and later opened an investigation on unpaid taxes covering activities between 2009 and 2018.

title: Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg lobbied against TikTok in Washington
text: Facebook CEO Mark Zuckerberg lobbied against TikTok in Washington months before President Trump threatened to ban the popular Chinese-owned app.

title: Facebook's Mark Zuckerberg reportedly warned Trump, lawmakers about rise of TikTok
text: The president issued an executive order targeting the popular video app TikTok earlier this month.

title: Facebook to pay 104 million euros in back taxes in France: media
text: Facebook France has accepted paying more than 100 million euros in taxes, including a penalty, relating to its accounting years before 2018, French financial magazine Capital reported on its website.
